oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Picture of Jinnie (Jennie) H. Fly and Amanda Felts
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Jinnie Fly, standing at the fence of what is assumed to be the family homestead. She is wearing all black, and is assumed to be in mourning. She appears to be in the later years of her life, and her attire seems like that of around the turn of the century. A young girl, presumed to be her niece Amanda Felts, stands on the other side of the fence, nearly out of frame.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Fly, Jinnie
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Tennessee State Library and Archives, Nashville, Davidson County, Tennessee
